# Guardian CODEOWNERS — review routing (PROPOSAL / interim).
#
# Named role owners do not yet exist (see docs/governance/CONTROL_OWNERS.md — all TBD).
# Until they are assigned, security-sensitive paths route to the accountable repository
# owner @INVIS-ABLE. This is interim, not a claim that separation-of-duties is complete:
# a HIGH/CRITICAL change still needs a SECOND independent human reviewer per the Merge
# Governor charter — CODEOWNERS approval alone does not satisfy that.
#
# Replace @INVIS-ABLE with the specific role owners from path_ownership.yaml as they are
# named, and enable "Require review from Code Owners" in the main ruleset (owner action).

# Default: repository owner is accountable for anything not otherwise routed.
